The U.S. Agriculture Department saidit has accepted a bid for an export bonus to cover the sale of18,000 tonnes of U.S. durum wheat to Algeria.    A bonus of 43.25 dlrs per tonne was awarded to Cam USA Incon the shipment scheduled for June 20-30, Melvin Sims, USDAgeneral sales manager, said.    An additional 228,000 tonnes of durum wheat are availableto Algeria under the department's export enhancement program,Sims said. Reuter&#3;